subsection.p:
To summarize,
if either a left- or right-hand limit fails to exist or if the left- and right-hand limits are not equal to each other,
the overall limit does not exist.

solution.p:
To see algebraically why this is the case, observe that

  \lim_{x \to -2} f(x) = \amp  \lim_{x \to -2} \frac{4-x^2}{x+2}
  = \amp  \lim_{x \to -2} \frac{(2-x)(2+x)}{x+2}
.

