note.p:
For a function f,
provided f^{-1} exists, the domain of f^{-1} is the range of f, and the range of f^{-1} is the domain of f;
f^{-1}(f(x)) = x for every x in the domain of f and f(f^{-1}(y)) = y for every y in the range of f;
y = f(x) if and only if x = f^{-1}(y).

